SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1112
By Southerland
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate the Greeneville
Emergency and Rescue Squad upon seventy-
five years of service.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly take great pride in recognizing those
honorable institutions that have operated throughout their existence for the betterment of this
State and the protection of its citizenry; and
WHEREAS, the Greeneville Emergency and Rescue Squad is one such venerable
institution that recently celebrated its seventy-fifth year of service; and
WHEREAS, founded in June 1950 and chartered in September of that same year, the
Greeneville Emergency and Rescue Squad has always stood as a dependable organization
whose members have served with constancy and valor in providing emergency care and
transport; and
WHEREAS, in 1950, the Greeneville Emergency and Rescue Squad received its first
vehicle, an ambulance donated by Kiser Funeral Home, and that same year, more than thirty
volunteers signed up for training with the squad; the squad's first building was completed in May
1951, and since 1973, the rescue squad has made its headquarters on West Church Street; and
WHEREAS, staffed entirely by volunteers, the Greeneville Emergency and Rescue
Squad serves Greene County in a number of ways, including responding to vehicle accidents,
assisting with natural disaster recovery, performing water rescues, conducting search
operations, and providing mutual aid to surrounding areas when needed; and
WHEREAS, the agency currently operates with twenty-two volunteers, and in 2024
alone, the rescue squad responded to more than 300 calls; and
WHEREAS, each member of the rescue squad is trained in CPR, first aid, emergency
vehicle operation, and basic extrication; additional specialized training is offered, including rope
SJR1112
017552
- 1 -

and swift water operations, structure collapse training, grain bin entrapment training, and farm
machinery accident training, among others; and
WHEREAS, because of the squad's remarkable efforts, countless lives have been saved
and many crises averted, all of which are just a part of the daily work of these dedicated
individuals; and
WHEREAS, this historic milestone marks a legacy of public service and resilience,
reflecting the squad's ability to adapt to changing times while remaining committed to its mission
of emergency response and lifesaving efforts; and
WHEREAS, for seventy-five years, the Greeneville rescue squad has been an integral
part of Greene County's emergency response network, and its members truly epitomize the
ideals of consummate professionals, dedicated public servants, and reliable friends and
neighbors; and
WHEREAS, since the establishment of the Greeneville Emergency and Rescue Squad,
its members have upheld the finest tenets and traditions of emergency service, and it is wholly
fitting that we recognize them for their many years of service to their community and this State;
now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate the members of the
Greeneville Emergency and Rescue Squad upon the celebration of the organization's seventy-
fifth anniversary, extending to them our best wishes for their every future success and thanking
them for their tireless and unwavering service to Greene County and this State.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
